section.p: The Subject Element template consolidates information about the timing of each subject's progress through the epochs and elements of the trial.

ol.li: SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @classCode="ACT" Act (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.6 HL7ActClass) (CONF:350)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @moodCode="EVN" Event (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.1001 HL7ActMood) (CONF:351)

SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] id (CONF:352)
The identifier is assigned to ensure uniqueness of the subject records within the domain. [SDTM: SESEQ]

SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] code (CONF:353), where the @code SHALL be selected from ValueSet Subject Element Set locally defined STATIC (CONF:1525)
The code value indicates the nature of the element. If the element is unplanned, the code value should indicate this. Uose original text to provide the verbatim content of the element - whether planned or unplanned. [SDTM: ETCD, ELEMENT, SEUPDES], [SEND: ETCD, ELEMENT, SEUPDES]

SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] effectiveTime (CONF:355)
Information that records the start and stop dates of the element. A value for the start date - interval lower bound is required. [SDTM: SESDTC, SEENDTC], [SEND: SESDTC, SEENDTC]

MAY contain zero or one [0..1] entryRelationship (CONF:356)
Records the study epoch during which the information was collected.
Contains @typeCode="REFR" REFR
Contains exactly one [1..1] Study Epoch (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.83)

MAY contain zero or one [0..1] entryRelationship (CONF:357)
Used to record the order of the element within the study arm to which the subject is assigned. It is used for human clinical trials, but not for non-human trials.
This entryRelationship SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @typeCode="REFR" (CONF:338)
This entryRelationship SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] observation (CONF:339)
This observation SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @classCode="OBS" Observation (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.6 HL7ActClass) (CONF:340)
This observation SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @moodCode="EVN" Event (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.1001 HL7ActMood) (CONF:343)
This observation SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] code (CONF:341), where the @code SHALL be selected from (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.3.26.1.1 NCI Thesaurus) (CONF:342)
The code value indicates the observation captures an element's order within a trial arm.
This observation SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] value with data type ED (CONF:344)
A value that gives the order of an element within the trial arm. Since this order could be hierachically represented as a collection of integers separated by ".", e.g., "2.1", the text (ED) data type is assigned.[SDTM: TAETORD]

SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] entryRelationship (CONF:358)
Identifies the SDTM or SEND domain the record is assigned to.
Contains @typeCode="REFR" REFR
Contains exactly one [1..1] Domain Assignment (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.30)

MAY contain zero or more [0..*] entryRelationship (CONF:359)
Establishes a relationship between this record and another record.
Contains @typeCode="REFR" REFR
Contains exactly one [1..1] Related Record (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.75)

MAY contain zero or more [0..*] entryRelationship (CONF:360)
Allows the association of a supplemental value - outside of the content specfied for the domain - to the record.
Contains @typeCode="COMP" COMP
Contains exactly one [1..1] Supplemental Value (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.96)

MAY contain zero or more [0..*] entryRelationship (CONF:361)
A place to insert comments related to a particular finding.
Contains @typeCode="COMP" COMP
Contains exactly one [1..1] Comment (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.23)

MAY contain zero or more [0..*] entryRelationship (CONF:362)
Allows recording of additional findings related to the element.
Contains @typeCode="COMP" COMP
Contains exactly one [1..1] Finding About (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.40)
